{
  "stem": "1965.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they took the hundreds of books, threw them out of the window in that yard-- while we stood there and watched-- and lit a bonfire on all these books.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "During that same day, as I'm watching, I'm holding this little boy, the one that previously stood besides me when the other children were taken away.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one person threw a stone at us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now please understand that in Belgium, there were two types of people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were the people who sacrificed and helped many Jews-- the non-Jews I'm speaking of now.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was a group of Belgium, non-Jews, who for every Jew they delivered to the Nazis, they would get paid.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What happened is they were known, believe it or not, as the [NON-ENGLISH]-- the blacks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it is those pro-Nazi helpers that did a lot of damages locally to us little children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were mocked.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We were-- we were beaten.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were hit, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But we survived each and every time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It is in that place that I started to dislike a vegetable known as turnips.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because that was, in that particular place, one of the main foods that was given to us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Have you ever taken a turnip, boil it, no salt, no nothing, and eat it like this?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yuck.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So until today, I never eat turnips, and I'm a vegetarian.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But thank God he created so many beautiful fruits and vegetables.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So there are choices galore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What was your daily routine like as a child in hiding?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The daily routine-- you got up, and you prayed that you could make the night-- so you can survive.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at night, when the sirens happened and the bombs were falling-- one night, I unfortunately I had dysentery.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
